-- Clippers Defeat Grizzlies, Move on to Face Spurs in NBA Playoffs
-- B y   R o b   G l o s t e r
-- 2012-05-13T19:46:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-13/clippers-defeat-grizzlies-move-on-to-face-spurs-in-nba-playoffs.html
Chris Paul scored 19 points to lead
the Los Angeles Clippers into the second round of the National
Basketball Association playoffs with an 82-72 defeat of the host
Memphis Grizzlies.  The Clippers, who won the best-of-seven series by four
games to three, will face the  San Antonio Spurs  in the second
round of the Western Conference playoffs.  Rudy Gay had 19 points and nine rebounds for Memphis, who
shot 33 percent from the field.  The Indiana Pacers play at the  Miami Heat  later today in
the opening second-round game in their Eastern Conference
playoff series. The Heat defeated the Knicks 4-1 in the first
round.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Rob Gloster at 
 rgloster@bloomberg.net  